## Best Practices

### 1. Always Use Services
```java
// ✅ CORRECT
InventoryService service = InventoryService.getInstance();
service.addProduct(product);

// ❌ AVOID
DatabaseQuery.insertProduct(product);  // Bypasses service layer
```

### 2. Handle Exceptions
All database operations may throw SQLException. Controllers use AlertUtil for user feedback:
```java
try {
    service.addProduct(product);
} catch (SQLException e) {
    AlertUtil.showError("Error", "Failed to add product");
}
```

### 3. Refresh After Updates
For other users/windows viewing same data:
```java
service.refresh();  // Reloads from database
tableView.refresh();  // Updates UI
```

## Performance Tips
1. Use categories to filter products - creates small result sets
2. Archive old orders regularly (optional future feature)
3. Index on order_date if querying by date range

